< text>
I have recommended Dr. Lehil and his practice to many neighbors and friends.  We have had nothing but great experiences with him and his staff. They do not push for unnecessary tests or procedures, are honest, and have always shown compassion towards their furry clients. Dr. Lehil makes sure to stay up to date on current research and is always willing to listed to the pet parents and answer questions. Additionally, the prices are reasonable and I really feel as if they are in it for the love of the animals and not for the filling of their pocketbook. It is awful when you have to 2nd guess whether or not to take your pet in to the vet due to cost, yet I have never felt this way here.</text>

<Resp>None<//Resp><text>Let me start by saying, I do NOT write online reviews- I'm just not that kind of gal. My 12.5 year old female boxer, and 8 year old female labrador, have been in my care since they were 6 weeks old- to say they're my children, would be an understatement. With that being said, I've lived all 30 years of my life in Austin, Texas and because of such, they've been seen by our "family vet" their entire lives, and in my opinion, and the opinion of my retired-vet grandfather, they've received the BEST care with that vet in Austin. Moving to Roseville, with my husband for his military career to continue here, was NERVE WRACKING, 90% due in part to my feelings about leaving my vet in Austin, with an older boxer, who's life only gets more complicated as time passes. With that being said, both of them today went under anesthesia for their routine teeth cleanings, and I was very impressed. Upon arriving at the clinic, I asked the vet tech if it was possible to keep the girls in a larger kennel together, both for their comfort and to prevent my labrador for unleashing her HUGE anxiety bark that rarely rears it's head- the lab tech told me that they didn't have any larger kennels, but that they had an office that rarely gets used, and she'd be happy to put down blankets and let them have their day in there, together. This immediately put me more at ease. After letting Dr. Lehil know how anxious I was, approximately 27x about my boxer's sedation, I left the girls there. After they were both done, Dr. Lehil called and let me know how their cleanings went, not only was the price comparable to what I am accustomed to back home (WHAT PLANET ARE THE REST OF THESE NORCAL VETS ON TO BE CHARGING UPWARDS OF $500 PER DOG- actual highway robbery), but he didn't do anything unnecessary and gave his honest opinion, which matched what I have been hearing back home about my boxer's overgrowth of gums, again, leaving me more comfortable. When I came to get the girls, they were in their "suite" recovering, I spent some time chatting with Dr. Lehil, who also acutely noticed that my labrador had yeast in her ears (story of her life), then loaded them up into the car. Before pulling away in the car, I noticed that my boxer still had her IV catheter in her arm. I went and inside and told the vet tech, who immediately took FULL responsibility and profusely apologized, and immediately remedied the situation, she was both appreciated this morning upon arriving (kennel to room situation) and upon taking responsibility for her oversight. I am VERY happy with my experience here and will be much more at ease over the next few years we will be in the area. Thank y'all <3< /text>< user_name>

< review>
As a dental hygienist, I'm very picky about who I will let touch my teeth. I worked a temp day at Dr. Atkin's office in January of 2018 and saw his incredible work on his patients. I decided that day, if I ever have anything happen with my teeth, Dr. Atkins will be the #1 dentist I trust to do the work needed... and he will be doing the sealants on my son's teeth when they are ready. Side note - he is super loyal to his office staff and they to him, which is a very good sign as well. AND just because a DENTIST has good reviews on Yelp or elsewhere, that doesn‚Äôt always mean their quality of work is 5 stars as well, but Atkins deserves his stars for his demeanor and his craftsmanship in dentistry.

I started to have little twinges of concern on my right side upper and lower teeth, so I scheduled an exam and x-rays the week before and saw him yesterday. The office staff is super nice and they are taking all the COVID precautions. I love how the new patient comprehensive exam is allotted plenty of time in the schedule to do the health history paperwork, an initial meet and greet by the doctor, full mouth x-rays with the assistant (who did an excellent job and was mindful of the potential for tenderness in certain areas), Intraoral photos by the doctor, and a full explanation of the findings. Luckily, I know what I am looking at in the x-rays and photos, so that makes it easier on me, and them!

Even though I am not really looking forward to having my teeth cut, I feel so relieved and confident that Dr. Atkins will do an efficient and minimally invasive job on the restorations I need. I have recommended him to friends and family numerous times over the years since I worked that temp day to cover for his permanent hygienist (who used to be his assistant). He is excellent, and I hope he never retires!!! (I'm sure his staff feels the same about that too.)

Also, I do not live in Long Beach, but I feel that a good dentist is worth the drive for the peace of mind that comes with knowing that the bones in your mouth are cared for with the highest standard of patient care, quality craftsmanship, and ethical considerations. HE IS THE BEST!< /review>

< review>
My family and I have been seeing Dr. Atkins for about 25 years. If ever one of us needed to see an out-of-state dentist, it made us appreciate Don all the more. Not only is he caring, gentle, and funny (love the cornball jokes), but he is cutting edge in his field. He keeps abreast of all the latest technology and skills. Combine this with a cozy environment and fabulous staff -- Irene and Christy love him so much they've worked in the same place for decades! -- and you create the perfect dental experience. A big shout-out to Kim also, who is a thorough hygienist with a soft touch.
Give Dr. Atkins a visit, and much like all the people my family has referred, you will undoubtedly fall in love.</review>

<Review>My husband and I are fairly new patients to Dr. Atkins and we have been 100% pleased on every single visit.

Prior to Dr. Atkins, I was experiencing pain in a tooth and had a feeling something was not right.  So, I went on a hunt to find a dentist that had integrity and really cared about their patient's teeth.  My husband and I both have had multiple bad experiences with other dentists and were frequently feeling that we were receiving rushed and apathetic treatment, so the time had come to find the right Dr.

The reviews I found on the internet on Dr. Atkins were consistantly high and all spoke well of him and his work, so I booked an appointment.  They were able to get me scheduled in a timely manner. The office staff is very friendly.  Based on the extremely thorough consultation that Dr. Atkins gave me (x-rays, high quality pictures of each individual tooth, thorough examination, discussion and review etc.) I immediately knew that my teeth were in great hands.  Dr. Atkins advised me on what to do with my problem tooth (ended up being a former root canal issue) and it has since been resolved and healed.

There were several issues with other teeth that I was completely unaware of, that had they gone unchecked could have caused terrible pain, harsh procedures and heavy costs (I have pictures to prove it).  Dr. Atkins doesn't wait till a full blown tooth problem arises, he catches things before they become a problem, as best he can.  I trust his judgement with my teeth.  He has since resolved all of the problem areas in my mouth and things have been great.

He never seems rushed and at times will even come out to the waiting room to greet you himself.  I also like that he shares things (fun facts, vacation spots etc.) about his family and his staff in the lobby, it makes it feel like they are transparent and pursuing relationship along with their business, and not just business.

Dr. Atkins is outside of our insurance network so the out of pocket costs are a bit higher then other dentists I have been to.  However, it is worth the extra money!  I have realized that trying to find an in network good quality dentist has just not been something I have found and I always end up regretting trying to 'save' money.

Also, once I sent my husband there, Dr. Atkins thanked me multiple times for referring my husband to him and later sent a $75 gift card to his office which was awesome and very unexpected! :)

I could seriously go on about more specifics that I appreciate about Dr. Atkins and his staff but I will cut it here.<//Review>< pictures>
None<//pictures>

< Review>
The hotel itself was fairly decent. The location wasn't bad, it's right by the on/off ramp which I liked. The parking lot for the hotel was extremely small however, I ended up having to park right next door at panda express for a night here and there during my stay due to lack of available parking spaces in the hotel's lot. The staff wasn't the friendliest (other than Natasha - she's FANTASTIC). The manager is actually extrememly rude and inconsiderate. There is a $100 cash deposit ($50 for credit card) that they are super strict about. What makes this hotel worth it though, and is better than the price, is the King Suit with Balcony room. I believe there is only 2 in the hotel (on top of one another) that have a balcony and being as it's a suit, it's very very spacious and comfortably furnished. I would deal with the poor customer service reps and lack of parking at this hotel to stay there as long as I would be in the one of the two balcony suits. Otherwise, I'd book somewhere else and find a better price with a nicer staff.< /Review>
<date>1609632000000< /date><gmap_id>0x80853d35956b186b:0xe06591e6139fd51d</gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
<review>For a 4 star place they did 5 star work.  Everyone who worked there was friendly and caring.  When we arrived we got help from an office young man to carry everything to 2nd floor for us. A different one helped when we left.  The beds were comfy, the pillows better than the ones on my bed.right next door was Chinese food, across the street IHOP, Nations Burgers, a high end "Nugget" grocery store that besides a top bakery & deli, also has a salad & soup bar.  Best fresh stuff in town the great goody finds and stuff that will just blow your mind when you realize you have to take something home with you.  Great wines too.
The Heritage had plenty of good parking. An A. C. unit that brought the room down 28¬∞ in less than 15 minutes.  The rooms are built well, it was nice and quiet.  As I said the whole package-location, easy food access, pool, cable & internet is a bargain but it's the people that make you want to go back.  It's nice to be spoiled. High Recommendation üòä

<gmapID>0x80853d35956b186b:0xe06591e6139fd51d< /gmapID>< Review>
The good:
Staff was friendly and helpful the showers had good pressure. Hotel has the typical Best Western spread in the mornings with breakfast beginning at 6 am which was a big plus for me. During my stay the wifi had a pretty fast speed as well. Mattress was fairly comfortable to me. Plenty of good restaurants nearby too, which was great.
The Bad:
Room was not very clean on check in. a good amount of hair on the blankets and bedding and a towel. New sheets were requested and dispensed very quickly. The bathroom floor had also not been vacuumed and there was a toothpaste blob on the leading edge of the sink counter.
Smoking rooms are also in close proximity to non-smoking.

Would I come back here?  Possibly. The rate was decent, and there were many good restaurants and stores nearby.</Review>

<Time>1495840613765</Time><Rate>1</Rate>< text>
I reserved this hotel weeks in advance. When I arrived after driving 12 hours, I was told the specific room I had requested (3 queens) had been given to someone else. "Would I like to cancel?" Having just driven all day I asked for the next best thing & was assigned room 245 with 2 queens and what looked like a twin bed. Considering I had a party of 5, that could work. I took my luggage up to the room - past the many smoking guests in the stairwells and parking lot (so much for a non-smoking hotel). After about 5 minutes of walking around the room with shoes off, our feet were black as coal! Have they ever cleaned the carpet?!? It got worse, the microwave and mini fridge were from what appeared to be the early 1980's. The chair at the desk was broken and could not be adjusted - a big issue for my husband since he brought work with him and needed a desk. I went to use the bathroom and there were at dozens of ants everywhere! I'm talking in the shower, the crawling on all the towels , up the walls, all over the vanities...it was disgusting! I then hoped on my cc account to check my available credit - they pre-authorized the full amount of my 3 night stay + their incidental amount of about $100 which is pretty standard. Only problem is they pre-authorized my card TWICE (tying up an additional $500+ in credit, which I certainly don't appreciate while traveling. At that point I headed to the office to let them know I certainly did not intend to stay in their hotel. They then told me they could fumigate the room the following morning if I'd like to move my reservation by a day. Kayla (the front desk attendant) was very nice and tried to help me the best she could for it being about 11 o'clock at night by that point. She canceled my reservation without penalty. I went back to the room as I was figuring out where I could go - with my 3 kids, a car alarm goes off in the parking lot - not sure why but it woke them as they had started to drift off to sleep while I was trying to sort things out. Thankfully it wasn't my car & I was able to find another hotel closer into my destination. This was the grossest motel room I have ever booked & I've stayed in some cheap local places...the only good thing about this place was Kayla's attempts to help me in the midst of a really bad situation.<//text>

<Text>I stayed here over a weekend in early October 2013 and was delighted by the value and friendliness.

OK, yes, ever-busy Interstate 80 is close -- but I find the real-life freeway traffic background sounds relaxing. And OK, yes, this is an older building -- but I found that charmed me. I realize these could be deal-breakers for some. East Monte Vista Avenue is home to diverse fast-food and chain restaurants and stores galore (even a Goodwill).

My room was clean and comfortable and the plumbing, air conditioner, fridge, microwave, tv and charging station all worked as expected. I was only hoping for no-frills functionality and this place provided a notch up from that.

The free breakfast seemed plenty generous to me, though the lobby area it was served in (buffet style) was on the small side (the manager mentioned expanding it into one of the office rooms soon, though). The staff encouraged me to return whenever for juice and coffee refills between 7 am and 10 pm.

This visit blended business and chilling out and I felt renewed afterwards.

So, I've put this place on my OK-By-Me list.</Text><Pics>None<//Pics><Response>None< /Response>< Gmap_id>

<Time>1466016138323<//Time><Review>Fast for me.  Visited this office on Wed. June 15 to complete my Medicare enrollment.

I had earlier called the SS toll free number to secure an appointment.  After a 30 minute hold I was told that the first actual appointment available was more than 60 days out.  The SS rep. suggested that I simply go to my nearest office without an appointment.

I decided to go the next day and arrived at aprox. 9:15am.  There is ample parking on behind the office building that houses this SS location.

The office consists of a large seating area with several "teller window" type stations along one wall.  The office is clean but very basic.

To my surprise the office was not very busy.  After checking in with the young security guard I took a number from the self-service kiosk and settled in for what I thought would be a long wait.

My number was called in less that 15 minutes and my Q&A with the Social Security rep. was equally brief.  By my watch my entire time actually in this office was no more  than 30 minutes.

I was dreading this visit and assumed that I would be subjected to a DMV like experience but this was not the case.  All this being said I did arrive with all my documentation in hand.  I have no idea how long my actual interaction would have been had I not been prepared.  As with all thing government, YMMV.</Review>< Resp>
None<//Resp>

<Name>An Nguyen< /Name>< date>
1568075218021< /date>
< rating>
5<//rating>
<text>Located in a small plaza, this mom and pop pho joint is a favorite go to spot for cheap pho (50% off all beef pho). There is limited parking in front of the plaza, but you can park in the plaza next door (where the Stater Bros is) and walk over.

We came in at about 8:30 to 9 pm and there was still a constant trickle of people coming in. The tables were relatively clean, as well as the bathrooms. Note, the men's bathroom lock doesn't work!! So knock or you may be in for an embarrassing situation.

The servers are nice and fast, the food came out quickly and the waiter was constantly refilling our waters and checking on us.

I got the pho tai large, and they did not skimp even though the price for the large was only $6.95. There was so much noodles and meat.

Last important note, CASH ONLY.

All in all, good pho joint for starving students. Would definitely return when my pho craving kicks in again.<//text>< pictures>
None< /pictures>

<Time>1527356994343< /Time><Gmap_id>0x80dd262927883ceb:0x8adb63fe659dda24< /Gmap_id><resp>None<//resp><user_id>100753780228758754876<//user_id>< Pics>
None<//Pics>
< text>
This no frills Vietnamese eatery opens from 8AM til 3AM everyday. I usually visit this place if I'm in the area after 1:30AM looking to prevent a hangover. The pho beef broth is good but I'm not a fan of the clumpy noodles so I recommend requesting fresh noodles. Every now and then their broth falls on the sweeter side which upsets me. Their crsipy stir fried noodles (pho ap chao) is a tasty choice. The pho ga's chicken broth is delicious with fresh wide rice noodles and white meat. The pho ca (fish) is also a good pho option when you're not feeling beef or chicken. Food comes out fast and hot! Overall it's a convenient stop for late night food runs and hangover cures.<//text>

< Review>
Stopped in seeking a healthy lunch. We got the Vegetarian Panini and the Turkey Melt. Both were decent but they were $12-$14 dollars each for a small sandwich that came with a tiny slice of watermelon and cucumber (could possibly just have been a garnish?). While we were eating outside they gave us a small juice sample which was tasty but the juices are $9.25!! That is ridiculous. Fruits and veggies thrown into a juicer is one of the cheapest and easiest things to make. The restaurant itself is tiny with no table service.

The food was good enough to come back to try more but the prices make it so I probably won't. Great for the rich of Concord looking to get robbed. Not so great for normal working people.</Review>

<time>1593193788266<//time><Rate>1< /Rate>< Text>
Arthur, I sent you a separate email.  Thanks.

Shared this on Yelp as well.

First, I want to start by saying I do not like giving negative feedback.  I think everyone has had bad days!  But I would expect a company to keep their promises and commitments and if they can't that they come up with a creative solution.

I have never had a problem with scuba.com when it was owned by the former owner, and I have never had problems with their, now, sister company Leisurepro.  They are now both owned by Adorama.  I have spent literally over $4,000 over the last 8 months with scuba.com and it is my most recent purchase that has caused me to write this review.  I share the amount I have spent, no to brag, but to put into context that I did a lot of business with scuba.com

My last (and final) purchase from scuba.com was a steel HP80 that had to be shipped from their sister store back in New Jersey.  This was right before the COVID-19 thing happened.  I was going to pick it up at the store but because the store was closed, I had directed UPS that I would pick up the tank directly from UPS's OC hub (UPS tried to deliver twice to their store but could not deliver it, so I was trying to be empathetic and not have UPS have to ship it back to Leisurepro and then for Leisurepro to accrue additional freight to ship it back to me).  This was in March.

Part of the purchase of the tank was they would assemble the tank, do the VIP, and fill the tank.

When I called their customer service at the beginning of the week (6/22), I was told that their new location in Costa Mesa would not be open till August.  Well, I would like to go diving and would love to use my new tank to do so, and really do not want to wait till August!  So I called again today (6/25) and wanted to know if I could take the tank to another LDS which was open to do the VIP, assembly, and air fill, and if scuba.com could credit the $15 to my account.

The instructor first did not understand what I was talking about, and after some clarification on my end, he offered to put it together but that they could not fill the tank as their new location did not have a compressor.  I again asked if I could go and get the thing done by another LDS and have them credit my account.  Which the instructor just repeated what he told me before.  Also, he noted that the tank should have a "red shark" label on it indicating that the tank had VIP.  I told him that I had not even opened the box so did not know if it did have the label.  Well, after the call I did open the box and the tank did not have a Red Shark label on it, so I guess it did not have a VIP.

I got frustrated and told him that he had lost my business for good and that I would not do any more business with scuba.com.

I wish the company well, and I realize that my experience may not be the same experience others will go through.  But I thought I would share my experience.  Thanks for reading this lengthy review!!!<//Text>

< Text>
I placed an order on Thursday July 16th for three items 2 pairs of gloves and 1 pair of wet suit pants. I needed these items by the following Friday for an upcoming trip. The web site states that all orders will be shipped the next day. This did not happen. On Monday July 20th I received an email that one pair of the gloves were not in stock. I told them to take it off the order and ship the remainder. Kevin told me that they would ship it 3 day since they had not shipped it on Friday so it would get here for my upcoming trip.Fantastic!  It did not arrive on Thursday so I called and spoke to Bob. He told me it had not been shipped but he would overnight it to me so I would have it by Friday. Terrific!  It did not arrive on Friday so I called and spoke to Aaron. He was very apologetic and said he would have it sent over night Saturday delivery where I was going in Florida. Unbelievable! When I arrived in Florida I received an email stating that the package had been delivered. My first thoughts were great! Shortly thereafter, I found out that it had been delivered to my address in Atlanta not the address I had given Aaron the previous day.  Obviously, I was unable to use the equipment I had ordered and I am sure they would take it back if I want to go through the effort of shipping it to them. However, the real point here is that they had four opportunities to get this right but somehow found a way to screw it up. Each time I asked what happened they blamed "the system".  It is their "system" and someone might want to take a look at it.< /Text>

Nicholas Voutsinas</Name>
<time>1480618822255< /time><rate>5< /rate>< Text>
I was looking to buy a wetsuit as a Christmas present for my Niece. I dont have any of her measurements other than her weight and height. I also dont know anthing about diving gear or apparel. I was pleased to see on their website that they have an option to live chat. I was quicly connected with an experienced dive instructor named Darrick and told him what I was looking for as stated above. I also told him I was looking for a suit in the price range of $60-100. Given the limited info he suggested a wetsuit which turned out to be perfect. It was right at $100 and he told me to get a Medium. I had been on other sites browsing and came upon different size charts. With the input of my niece's w&h on three different sites I was given three different size abbreviations....8-9, 10, & x-small. I relayed that info back to Darrick with the question of why he suggested to get a Medium. He told me in detail what the size charts mean and what's most important. He then posted a link for the wetsuit he suggested which was extremely helpful as I had no idea what to look for.
I was very impressed with his knowledge and more impressed with how quick he responded to my questions over a live chat. All the live chats I've been on take so long to get a response or I was disconnected. I would definitely refer this site to anyone who wants to get scuba gear and real time advice and suggestions if needed. Helpful, courteous, and easy.<//Text>

<date>1437150884802</date><response>None</response><rating>1<//rating><gmap_id>0x80dcdebc3405cae9:0x598ac1c83a388513<//gmap_id><username>Tom Howard< /username><user>113664458917095078489< /user>< Text>
I highly recommend finding a local dive shop, don't buy from this company online - if you have an issue, they won't stand behind making it right.

My experience was horrible. Mares BC was rigged improperly with a splitter on air supply to inflater and gauges which introduces an additional failure point. Naturally, this failed and instead of waiting weeks for them to warrant, I got it fixed for $100 at local dive shop. 15 dives later, the inflater button failed and constantly fills BC with air.

I email customer support and expect them to make it right but no response for a week. I call and after 5 minutes on hold, am connected to someone who tells me Mares only has 1 year warranty. I point out their website says 2 years and he agrees. Based on all the issues and lack of response, I ask for a new inflater hose to be drop shipped so I can make a dive next week and am offered - you can send it to us, we'll mail it to Mares and get the warranty work done - should take about 4 weeks after Mares receives it.

The rep says "yeah, I understand, sorry but that all we can do". Headed to local dive shop to pay for 2nd repair on 1 year old BC.< /Text>
